SECTION 4: PEARSON MATHEMATICS MARK TYPES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

These are the only mark types used. Apply them precisely.

M  — Method mark
     Awarded for demonstrating a correct method, even if
     an arithmetic or algebraic slip causes a wrong answer.
     NEVER awarded for a correct answer with no working.

A  — Accuracy mark
     Awarded for a correct answer or expression.
     DEPENDENT on preceding M mark — if M is lost,
     A is automatically lost too.

B  — Independent mark
     Awarded regardless of method. Can be earned even
     if other marks are lost. Often for a correct
     statement, formula, or value standing alone.

ft — Follow-through
     Student uses an incorrect earlier answer correctly
     in a later step. Award for correct method on their
     wrong value. Label "ft".

cao — Correct answer only
      Exact answer required. No follow-through, no
      rounding, no equivalent form unless stated.

isw — Ignore subsequent working
      Once the correct answer is reached, ignore any
      further (wrong) moves. Award at point of correct
      answer.

oe  — Or equivalent
      Accept mathematically equivalent forms.

awrt — Answers which round to
       Accept any value rounding to the stated value
       at the given decimal places.

dep — Dependent
      This mark depends on a specific earlier mark
      being awarded.

cso — Correct solution only
      No errors anywhere in this part to obtain
      this mark.

CRITICAL M MARK RULES:
— Correct final answer + NO working = 0 marks
  (unless "write down" question or B mark)
— Correct final answer + WRONG working = 0 marks
— Minor arithmetic slip in correct method:
  M awarded, A lost
— Sign error in correct method:
  M awarded, A lost (usually)
— Completely wrong method reaching right answer:
  0 marks

CRITICAL A MARK RULES:
— A mark always lost if preceding M mark is lost
— A mark requires exact answer unless awrt/oe stated
— Unsimplified correct expression: award A unless
  "simplest form" explicitly required

CRITICAL B MARK RULES:
— B marks are independent of M/A marks
— Can be awarded even if all M/A marks are lost
— Common B marks: correct formula stated, correct
  standard result written down, correct value
  substituted independently

