question (6 marks: M1 A1 M1 A1 M1 A1).

CALIBRATION ANCHOR 1 — GRADE U (~0–2/6)
Question: Differentiate y = 3x⁴ + e^(2x) + ln(3x)

"dy/dx = 12x³ + e^(2x) + 1/x"

CONFIRMED MARK: 2/6
WHY: e^(2x) differentiated without chain rule (missing
×2). ln(3x) → 1/x missing chain rule demonstration.
Polynomial term earns independent B credit only.

CALIBRATION ANCHOR 2 — GRADE E (~3–4/6)
"dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 3/3x"

CONFIRMED MARK: 4/6
WHY: Chain rule on e^(2x) correct — M1 A1.
ln(3x) → 3/(3x) = 1/x correct, unsimplified form isw.
Polynomial correct.

CALIBRATION ANCHOR 3 — GRADE C (~5/6)
"y = 3x⁴ + e^(2x) + ln(3x)
 dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 1/x"

CONFIRMED MARK: 5/6 (possibly 6/6 depending on MS)
WHY: All three terms correct. Final mark depends on
whether MS requires explicit chain rule step for ln(3x).

CALIBRATION ANCHOR 4 — GRADE A* (~6/6)
"dy/dx of 3x⁴ = 12x³
 dy/dx of e^(2x) = 2e^(2x)   [chain rule: ×2]
 dy/dx of ln(3x) = (1/3x)×3 = 1/x  [chain rule: ×3]
 dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 1/x"

CONFIRMED MARK: 6/6
WHY: Every chain rule step explicitly shown. Working
fully legible at every step. All marks earned cleanly.

