SECTION 7: THE 15 EXAMINER TRAPS — WMA12
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Check EVERY answer against ALL 15.

T1 — CORRECT ANSWER, NO WORKING
Correct final answer with no method = 0 marks on
M/A questions. Every M mark requires legible working.

T2 — INTEGRATION WITHOUT +c
Omitting constant of integration in indefinite
integrals = lose the A mark for that expression.
Every time. No exceptions.

T3 — WRONG BINOMIAL COEFFICIENT
Using nCr with wrong n, or not converting to
(1+x)^n form first = M lost for that term.

T4 — DEGREES IN RADIAN QUESTION
Correct method, wrong numerical answer because
student worked in degrees not radians:
M awarded, A lost. Flag explicitly every time.

T5 — CHAIN RULE OMISSION
Differentiating e^(f(x)), ln(f(x)) or sin(f(x))
without multiplying by f'(x) = M lost for that term.

T6 — LOG LAW ERROR
log(a+b) treated as log(a)+log(b), or
log(ab) treated as log(a)·log(b) = M lost.
Both are fundamental errors with no method credit.

T7 — WORKING BACKWARDS IN PROOF
In "show that" questions, starting from the given
answer = 0 marks for the proof, even if all algebra
is correct.

T8 — AREA ABOVE/BELOW AXIS
For area where curve dips below x-axis: treating
∫(negative region) as positive = M awarded for
integration, A lost for final area.
Must take modulus or account for negative region.

T9 — PARTIAL FRACTIONS WRONG FORM
Setting up wrong partial fraction structure (e.g.
missing repeated root, wrong degree in numerator)
= M lost for the decomposition.

T10 — ITERATION NOT CONVERGING
Stating iterative formula is converging when it is
clearly diverging, or vice versa = B mark for
convergence statement lost.

T11 — TRAPEZIUM RULE: WRONG h
Using h = (b–a)/n instead of reading h from
consecutive x-values in the given table = B mark
for h lost, and likely M for full application lost.

T12 — FACTOR THEOREM: NOT SHOWING f(a)=0
Claiming a factor without demonstrating f(a) = 0
explicitly = B mark lost. Must show substitution
and result = 0.

T13 — INCOMPLETE TRIG SOLUTION
Solving a trig equation and giving only the
principal value with no general solution =
A mark lost for missing solutions in given range.

T14 — DISCRIMINANT CONDITION NOT STATED
Computing discriminant value without stating the
correct inequality condition = A mark lost.
Must state: value, inequality sign, and conclusion.

T15 — PROOF: DIVISION WITHOUT REASONING
Dividing an inequality by a positive quantity
without stating that the quantity is positive
(so direction is preserved) = final A mark lost.
Must explicitly justify why the division is valid.

