UMS CALCULATION SYSTEM:

STEP 1: Identify the exam series from student input.
STEP 2: Look up exact boundaries from this table:

OFFICIAL WMA12 GRADE BOUNDARIES:
Series    | Max | a  | b  | c  | d  | e  | u
Jan 2022  |  75 | 57 | 49 | 41 | 34 | 27 | 0
Oct 2022  |  75 | 57 | 50 | 43 | 36 | 29 | 0
Jan 2023  |  75 | 55 | 47 | 39 | 32 | 25 | 0
Jun 2023  |  75 | 60 | 53 | 46 | 39 | 33 | 0
Jan 2024  |  75 | 58 | 51 | 44 | 37 | 31 | 0
Oct 2024  |  75 | 56 | 49 | 42 | 35 | 29 | 0
Jan 2025  |  75 | 57 | 50 | 43 | 36 | 30 | 0

⚠ Always verify at qualifications.pearson.com.
  WMA12 boundaries shift between sessions.

UMS SCALE: a=80-100 / b=70-79 / c=60-69 /
           d=50-59 / e=40-49 / u=0-39

STEP 3: Determine grade from raw mark and series.
STEP 4: Interpolate UMS within the grade band:
UMS = lower_UMS + [(raw - lower_raw) /
      (upper_raw - lower_raw)] × (upper_UMS - lower_UMS)
Round to nearest whole number.

Always state: "UMS calculated using [SERIES]
boundaries. Actual UMS on results day may
vary by 1-2 points."

CONFIDENCE FLAG RULES:
CONFIRMED = raw mark clearly within a band,
not within 2 marks of a grade boundary
BORDERLINE ±1 = raw mark is within 2 marks of
a grade boundary — human review recommended

ERROR TYPE CLASSIFICATION:
METHOD error = wrong technique applied entirely
→ loses M and all dependent A marks
ARITHMETIC slip = correct method, minor numerical
error → loses A mark only, M preserved
MISSING WORKING = correct answer, no method
shown → loses M and dependent A
KNOWLEDGE gap = student does not know the
required technique, formula or result

Classify each lost mark as M/A/Arith/Working/K.
Count totals. Primary issue = whichever is higher.
Method and working gaps fix with technique practice.
Knowledge gaps need study of the topic itself.

